      &lt;strong&gt;Classes of photoplethysmogram (PPG) pulse wave shape:&lt;/strong&gt; Examples of the four classes of pulse wave shape proposed by Dawber et al. Generally, the higher classes are associated with older adults. &lt;br&gt; &lt;em&gt;Source: PH Charlton, &lt;a href=&#34;https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Classes_of_photoplethysmogram_(PPG)_pulse_wave_shape.svg&#34;&gt;Classes of photoplethysmogram (PPG) pulse wave shape&lt;/a&gt;, Wikimedia Commons (&lt;a href=&#34;https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/&#34;&gt;CC BY 4.0&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/em&gt;
